China’s Hangzhou Suspends Electric Taxi Operations After Fire, News Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-12T03:06:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/china-s-hangzhou-suspends-electric-taxi-operations-after-fire-news-says.html
China ’s eastern city of Hangzhou
suspended operations of electric taxis today after a taxi
spontaneously caught fire yesterday, local newspaper Qiangjiang
Evening News reported.  The taxi company and vehicle producer are investigating the
accident, which caused no casualties. The tourist city started
to use some electric vehicles as taxis about three months ago,
the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  